          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Chicken thighs"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "ce2af6fb-d8d0-49c5-870a-5b59c1b749e4",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Seasonings"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "7184d136-94bf-4736-ac39-1d7492d807b4",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Jarred Artichoke Hearts + liquid"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "9e04ecd4-43a5-460b-b481-3ed717bb41be",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Julienne Cut Sun-Dried Tomatoes"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "a2d12ffe-f437-44ab-b70f-3534795ccd8a",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Garlic"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "2af8834c-cdec-43fa-adbe-792dc5ab6946",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "HOW TO MAKE THIS CROCK POT CHICKEN THIGHS RECIPE:"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "e791636d-b307-47a0-b8d3-4b2e7e9295b8",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Start by spraying a 6-quart crock pot/slow cooker with cooking spray."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "2b20e2ad-81a2-4818-81ac-33533a35ea5e",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Next, season chicken thighs with salt, pepper, and dried oregano. Transfer chicken thighs to the slow cooker in one layer."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "3e1f7933-88a6-401d-8e3f-6c16ef4d3f53",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Then, layer the artichoke hearts over the chicken and sprinkle with garlic. Take a 1/3-cup of the liquid from the jar with the artichoke hearts and pour it over the top."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "a5ddd101-7436-45d4-bcfe-c828b4c6adeb",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Next, cover; cook on HIGH for 4 to 4-1/2 hours, or on LOW for about 6 hours."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "606b9da6-1b74-4670-9dba-ffc39c5a0602",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Add in the sun-dried tomatoes 30 minutes before chicken is done cooking."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "720555a7-dba9-464c-9719-46e4d287c4ad",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Finally, sprinkle with fresh parsley and serve."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "aec5a1b5-fcc2-4cd0-b83a-ee7a8755c7f7",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "6a3e41bc-d2f0-47dd-bb89-46486f0364f3",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "CAN I USE CHICKEN BREASTS INSTEAD?"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "72872574-833e-4821-9bc0-83f3ac2dbd59",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Yes, you can absolutely use chicken breasts, but keep in mind that chicken breasts will need less time cooking, so start checking around 5-hour mark if cooking on LOW, and around the 3-hour mark if cooking on HIGH."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "fd7a58f6-7d7a-450b-81a0-97ba1e9ff629",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "CAN I USE BONE-IN CHICKEN THIGHS?"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "481a0d93-9083-418c-903e-ec33df012423",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Yes, using bone-in chicken thighs is fine. They might take a bit longer to cook; about 20 minutes longer in the crock pot."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "ce86f81c-3b4f-4a5b-89e3-f8df219a143b",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "CAN I DOUBLE THE RECIPE?"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "0d91ff8e-cd4f-46ef-91ca-bbeac55d80b2",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "I have always read not to use too many pieces of meat in a slow cooker. I think up to 6 is a good number, maybe even 8, depending on their size, but anything more than that might get a bit crowded. You want them all in one layer, slightly overlapping so to make room for the rest of the ingredients."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "23b36b25-58c8-427d-865c-c1cfa99a4766",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "HOW TO STORE CROCK POT CHICKEN THIGHS"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "3f8c6551-40d0-4c8d-868a-2676731d0823",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Your crock pot chicken thighs should be cooled and refrigerated 2 hours after cooking."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "8f617bc2-528d-4173-b2e1-fc5f6f72a37f",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Keep them stored in your fridge in an airtight container for 3 to 4 days."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "e2d1eef7-2357-4528-bd2a-91b85cf0331d",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "You can also freeze them. Let the chicken thighs cool completely; transfer to a freezer bag and place in the freezer. Keep frozen for up to 3 months."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "ed0d213d-8e00-48e8-b0a7-8409cdf31cd2",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "HOW TO REHEAT CHICKEN THIGHS"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "f821a464-5066-48e7-8291-dccffb084950",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Place chicken thighs on a baking sheet and reheat in a 350\u02daF oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until heated through."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "f77ae0ae-4e30-4ee6-b604-448992f4a723",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "TIPS FOR USING YOUR CROCKPOT"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "dae335e5-125a-4113-847d-615cca9dc5ea",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Use the right size crock pot."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "dbc534d4-cb8e-4003-a83f-68d4d082c2f4",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Coating the inside of the crock pot with a non-stick spray can prevent the need for scrubbing later."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "79e4a201-9870-4ce9-873e-aa79f6888832",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "For most crock pots, the high setting is about 280\u02daF, and the low setting is around 170\u02daF."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "c1f6e698-4d8c-4e91-9bf5-fecb150d5929",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Cooking on HIGH for one hour is about equal to cooking on the low setting for two hours."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "b099c3e2-51d5-4632-a54a-c0c742d12cf1",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Add fresh herbs at the end to keep flavors bright and fresh."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "8ae69d77-384a-488f-ba47-15300a59d0d8",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Place hard vegetables, like potatoes, carrots, and other root vegetables at the bottom of the slow cooker where they will have more moisture and cook thoroughly."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "d5c5e74e-92bf-491a-95d1-05f5603367e2",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Use cheaper cuts of meat. Inexpensive cuts of meat are often high in fat or connective tissue, both of which break down during long hour cooking methods."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "889ca063-82eb-400e-97f3-329d03603f38",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Add dairy at the end. Milk, cream, and other dairy products can break down and coagulate if overheated. Stir the dairy products into crock pot in the last 15-30 minutes, so it has just enough time to heat through."
        }
      ],
      "instruction": "See original recipe for details."
    }
  ]
}